    "He published the first book about August Macke in 1922 shortly after his death.": [],
    "In 1928, he integrated the picture gallery of the Kunstmuseum into the new building of the museum.": [],
    "When the Nazi racial laws took effect in 1933, Cohen, who was Christian but from Jewish lineage, was forced to retire as an undesirable \u201cnon-Aryan.\u201d A claim for re-establishment of service was rejected.": [],
    "Despite difficult economic conditions and health problems, Cohen worked as a private art appraiser.": [],
    "Increasing persecution followed him; he was prohibited to enter his former workplace, forced to move residences numerous times, and ultimately required to divorce his non-Jewish wife (1942).": [],
    "In 1941, he was arrested for \u201calleged aid to fraud by backdating.\u201d These charges were later dropped, but Cohen was convicted early in 1942 of trivial unlawful acts.": [],
